Use this board game asset pack for polished game visuals.

**GAME BOARD GRID** — Alternating square grid (chess/checkers style):
```css
.board { display:grid; gap:0; border:4px solid #5c3d2e; border-radius:4px; box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.4); }
.cell { width:64px; height:64px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; transition:background 0.15s; cursor:pointer; }
.cell:hover { filter:brightness(1.15); }
.cell-light { background:#f0d9b5; }
.cell-dark { background:#b58863; }
```

**DICE** — SVG dice face renderer:
```js
function renderDie(value) {
  const dots = {1:[[25,25]],2:[[12,12],[38,38]],3:[[12,12],[25,25],[38,38]],4:[[12,12],[38,12],[12,38],[38,38]],5:[[12,12],[38,12],[25,25],[12,38],[38,38]],6:[[12,12],[38,12],[12,25],[38,25],[12,38],[38,38]]};
  const pips = (dots[value]||[]).map(([x,y])=>`<circle cx="${x}" cy="${y}" r="4" fill="#1a1a1a"/>`).join('');
  return `<svg viewBox="0 0 50 50" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><rect width="50" height="50" rx="8" fill="#fefef8" stroke="#d1d5db" stroke-width="1.5"/>${pips}</svg>`;
}
```
Usage: `element.innerHTML = renderDie(4)` for a die showing 4.

**GAME TOKENS** — Colored circular tokens:
```css
.token { width:48px; height:48px; border-radius:50%; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-weight:700; font-size:18px; box-shadow:0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3), inset 0 2px 4px rgba(255,255,255,0.3); transition:transform 0.2s; cursor:pointer; }
.token:hover { transform:scale(1.1); }
.token-white { background:radial-gradient(circle at 35% 35%, #f8f8f8, #d1d5db); color:#374151; border:2px solid #9ca3af; }
.token-black { background:radial-gradient(circle at 35% 35%, #4b5563, #111827); color:#f9fafb; border:2px solid #374151; }
.token-red { background:radial-gradient(circle at 35% 35%, #ef4444, #991b1b); color:#fff; border:2px solid #b91c1c; }
.token-blue { background:radial-gradient(circle at 35% 35%, #3b82f6, #1e40af); color:#fff; border:2px solid #2563eb; }
```

**SCORE DISPLAY:**
```css
.score-panel { background:#1e293b; color:#f1f5f9; padding:12px 20px; border-radius:10px; font-family:monospace; box-shadow:inset 0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); }
.score-panel .label { font-size:11px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1px; color:#94a3b8; }
.score-panel .value { font-size:28px; font-weight:700; }
```

**TURN INDICATOR:**
```css
.turn-indicator { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:8px; padding:6px 14px; border-radius:20px; font-size:13px; font-weight:600; }
.turn-indicator.active { background:#22c55e; color:#fff; animation:pulse-turn 1.5s infinite; }
.turn-indicator.waiting { background:#374151; color:#9ca3af; }
@keyframes pulse-turn { 0%,100%{box-shadow:0 0 0 0 rgba(34,197,94,0.4)} 50%{box-shadow:0 0 0 8px rgba(34,197,94,0)} }
```

IMPORTANT: Use the grid system for any board-based game. Use tokens for player pieces. Use renderDie() for dice. Use score-panel for all score displays.
